National Telecommunica­tions Company, Globacom, has congratulated Nigerian Christians on the celebra­tion of Christmas which commemorates the birth of Jesus Christ. The Company in a state­ment in Lagos on Thursday urged them to spread the vir­tues of love, joy and peace as symbolized by Jesus Christ. Globacom encouraged the Christian faithful to be their brother’s keeper by showing love while praying for the up­liftment of the nation. It stat­ed that Christmas is known the world over as a season of love, brotherliness and affection. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! According to the compa­ny, “Christ came to the world in human form to show the love of God towards man­kind. His love and concern for humanity are shown by the sacrifice He made by leading man back to God. Jesus made himself a per­fect example of the values of love, humility, kindness, righteous living and fruits of the spirit which would guar­antee eternal life”, Glo said “We all should al­low the birth of the Prince of Peace to engender prog­ress and amity in the society by displaying acts of good neigh bourliness, selflessness and unity amongst citizen”. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION